{"questionId":"28037","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><strong>Some medical conditions require patients to take medication regularly for long&nbsp;periods of time. In this question, you will explore the concentration of a medicinal&nbsp;drug in the body, when the drug is given repeatedly.</strong></p>\n<p><br>Once a drug enters the body, it is absorbed into the blood. As the body breaks down the&nbsp;drug over time, the concentration of the drug decreases. Let <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>C</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>)</mo></math>, measured in milligrams&nbsp;per millilitre (<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>mg</mtext><mo> </mo><msup><mtext>ml</mtext><mrow><mo>−</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>) , be the concentration of the drug, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi></math> hours after the drug is given to the&nbsp;patient. The rate at which the drug is broken down is modelled as directly proportional to its&nbsp;concentration, leading to the differential equation</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>C</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mi>k</mi><mi>C</mi></math>, where&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi><mo>∈</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℝ</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></math>.</p>\n<p>The initial concentration is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>d</mi><mo> </mo><mtext>mg</mtext><mo> </mo><msup><mtext>ml</mtext><mrow><mo>−</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>d</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>For the remainder of this question, you will consider a particular drug where it is known&nbsp;that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn></math>. The first dose is given at time <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math> and it is assumed that before this there&nbsp;is no drug present in the blood.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The drug is to be given every <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi></math> hours and in constant doses, such that the concentration of&nbsp;the drug is increased by an amount <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>d</mi><mo> </mo><msup><mtext>mg ml</mtext><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math> . To simplify the model, it is assumed that each&nbsp;time the drug is given the concentration of the drug in the blood increases instantaneously.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Immediately after the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mtext>th</mtext></math>&nbsp;dose is given, the concentration of the drug is</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>d</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><msup><mtext>e</mtext><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>T</mi></mrow></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mtext>e</mtext><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>T</mi></mrow></msup><mo>+</mo><mo>…</mo><mo>+</mo><msup><mtext>e</mtext><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mi>T</mi></mrow></msup></mrow></mfenced></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>After a patient has been taking this drug for a long time, it is required to keep the&nbsp;concentration within a particular range so that it is both safe and effective.</p>\n<p>Let <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>H</mi><mi>n</mi></msub></math> be the highest concentration of the drug in the body for the interval&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mi>T</mi><mo>≤</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>n</mi><mi>T</mi></math>.</p>\n<p>Let <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>L</mi><mi>n</mi></msub></math> be the lowest concentration of the drug in the body for the interval&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mi>T</mi><mo>≤</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>n</mi><mi>T</mi></math>.&nbsp;This is shown in the following graph.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/c339152d5b9fa4a618694487327053fad48b741a.png\"></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>H</mi><mo>∞</mo></msub></math>&nbsp;is defined as&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>→</mo><mo>∞</mo></mrow></munder><msub><mi>H</mi><mi>n</mi></msub></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>L</mi><mo>∞</mo></msub></math>&nbsp;is defined as&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>→</mo><mo>∞</mo></mrow></munder><msub><mi>L</mi><mi>n</mi></msub></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Show that</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>H</mi><mo>∞</mo></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>L</mi><mo>∞</mo></msub><mo>=</mo><mi>d</mi></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>H</mi><mo>∞</mo></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>L</mi><mo>∞</mo></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>d</mi><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><msup><mtext>e</mtext><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>T</mi></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><msup><mtext>e</mtext><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>T</mi></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><msup><mtext>e</mtext><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>T</mi></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><msup><mtext>e</mtext><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>T</mi></mrow></msup></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><msup><mtext>e</mtext><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>T</mi></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mi>d</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 2</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>H</mi><mo>∞</mo></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>L</mi><mo>∞</mo></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>d</mi><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><msup><mtext>e</mtext><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>T</mi></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi>d</mi><mrow><msup><mtext>e</mtext><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>T</mi></mrow></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><msup><mtext>e</mtext><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>T</mi></mrow></msup><mo>-</mo><mi>d</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>d</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>d</mi><msup><mtext>e</mtext><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>T</mi></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><msup><mtext>e</mtext><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>T</mi></mrow></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><msup><mtext>e</mtext><mn>0</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mtext>e</mtext><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>T</mi></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mfenced><mrow><msup><mtext>e</mtext><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>T</mi></mrow></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mtext>e</mtext><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>T</mi></mrow></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><msup><mtext>e</mtext><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>T</mi></mrow></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mtext>e</mtext><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>T</mi></mrow></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mi>d</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>M1A0 </strong></em>for the use of their formulae from part (e). <br>Award <em><strong>M0A0</strong> </em>if at no point&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>→</mo><mo>∞</mo></math>&nbsp;in their response.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"28037","referenceCode":"22N.3.AHL.TZ0.2f.i","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"H∞-L∞=d.","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"f.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.9—Log laws"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}